cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.IT 

This paper deals with strategic reasoning and information processing in competitive environments, which are key topics in game theory (cs.GT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of information theory to analyze the behavior of expert and novice players also suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the concept of information encryption and the study of how experts conceal valuable information relates to cryptography (cs.CR) and information theory (cs.IT).
